Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.19,0:01:37.42,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Who was it, nii-sama...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.45,0:01:41.56,Style1,,0000,0000,0000,,that said cannibalism was true love?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.17,0:01:43.70,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Edgar Allan Poe?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.39,0:01:48.53,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No, nee-sama. He was a necrophiliac.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.84,0:01:56.92,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Richard Matheson?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.84,0:01:59.09,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\fnEssai\fs25\fad(200,200)}Richard Matheson: An American fantasy, sci-fi, horror author
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.16,0:01:59.08,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It could have been.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.72,0:02:04.45,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think they smelled this scent?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.84,0:02:18.58,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The fragrance of life flowing out.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.58,0:02:20.81,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The aroma of rust and saliferous liquid.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.34,0:02:23.79,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The scent when people breathe their last breath.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.45,0:02:27.52,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We're spoiled, nee-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.93,0:02:31.61,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They're going to make their move soon,\nthe people of this city.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.67,0:02:37.28,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is the eighth person we didn't plan on killing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.83,0:02:41.37,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone is going to try and kill us.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.93,0:02:44.10,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it exciting, nee-sama?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.10,0:02:45.71,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, nii-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.36,0:02:49.46,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm really excited.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.25,0:02:57.60,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, Lagoon Company.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.39,0:02:59.86,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Boris-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.65,0:03:03.13,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're cancelling the meeting?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.13,0:03:04.54,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.23,0:03:07.91,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll contact you as soon as the Kapitan's schedule opens up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.81,0:03:10.32,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's up, Rock?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.32,0:03:14.43,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He says the meeting is cancelled.\NI wonder if they had an emergency.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.88,0:03:16.66,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You think it's because of "that", Dutch?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.66,0:03:19.39,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it's been a big fuss.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.39,0:03:20.68,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's this about?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.68,0:03:24.16,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What? Haven't you heard anything about it, Rock?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.16,0:03:25.20,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.20,0:03:27.18,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Murder. It was a murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.18,0:03:31.37,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I hate to say it, but murder doesn't\nseem like that big a deal in this city.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.69,0:03:38.03,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Murder itself isn't rare, but it's different\nif they're targeting Hotel Moscow.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.04,0:03:40.61,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hotel Moscow?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.61,0:03:44.87,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There have been five Russian corpses so far this month.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.10,0:03:48.58,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Revy, that information is a bit outdated.\NRight now, there are six.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.10,0:03:54.40,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever it may be, there are some guys out\nthere that want to cause problems, Rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.06,0:04:00.92,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In this city, where the power balance between\nfactions is perched on its hands on a tightrope...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.84,0:04:04.60,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,it won't end without more blood being spilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.61,0:04:11.82,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Another one has been killed.\NThis time it was an accountant.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.82,0:04:15.12,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is this place Beirut or Mogadishu?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.12,0:04:16.84,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it, Balalaika.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.16,0:04:19.78,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's why we're having a liaison conference.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.42,0:04:22.17,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is an era of coexistence.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.17,0:04:28.26,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to keep the equilibrium we've gained\nthrough the bloodshed and bullets, Miss Balalaika.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.56,0:04:34.33,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Chang, when did I say that I wanted to coexist?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.38,0:04:37.63,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You sure talk big, Fry Face.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.63,0:04:41.14,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\fnEssai\fs25\fad(200,200)}Ivan refers to the farmer in "The Tale of Ivan the Fool" by Leo Tolstoy
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.63,0:04:41.14,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It makes me laugh when a country\NIvan like you tries to act like a queen.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.67,0:04:44.60,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\fnEssai\fs25\fad(200,200)}Sovkhoz is short for "Sovetskoe khoziastvo",  a state farm
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.67,0:04:44.60,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you go back to your\nsovkhoz and dig up potatoes?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.17,0:04:50.66,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\fnEssai\fs25\fad(200,200)}Guido: stereotypical male working class Italian-American usually from \NNew York
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.17,0:04:50.48,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard that Guido guts smell just like pigs.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.66,0:04:52.38,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is this true, Verrocchio?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.38,0:04:53.31,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You bitch!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.31,0:04:55.26,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hold your tongues, you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.77,0:04:58.90,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you think we're having this meeting?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.61,0:05:03.15,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We all hold unforgettable grudges against each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.71,0:05:07.61,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But, these are the times where\nwe cooperate for shared profit.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.26,0:05:11.31,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing else matters, if it benefits our businesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.31,0:05:17.21,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Feed that trivial honor to the dogs.\NIsn't that what the mafia is about?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.31,0:05:21.85,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Balalaika, you may be hearing this for the first time,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.62,0:05:25.87,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,but some of my men have been killed as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.73,0:05:30.26,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My affiliates from 14K and a\nmember of my executive staff.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.01,0:05:35.85,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In the red light district on Lachada Street, the\ncriminal's method was the same as with yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.15,0:05:38.10,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, Chang?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.96,0:05:41.56,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Someone is trying to break the balance!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.97,0:05:43.98,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Abrego! look at me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.01,0:05:51.84,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't kid around, Balalaika! Sure, I've fought with\nyou before, but we've resolved that already!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.55,0:05:57.12,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Then, Abrego, ask Verrocchio about the real killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.12,0:05:58.79,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Fuck off, Fry Face!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.54,0:06:02.47,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,One of our leg-breakers got nailed too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.47,0:06:04.75,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So, this makes nine bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.75,0:06:10.68,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Chang, this isn't the style of anyone\nin the city. A stranger did this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.33,0:06:13.81,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Someone who doesn't know how this city works.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.14,0:06:21.17,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Then let us conclude that this was an act of an outsider,\nand the committee will collaborate and go after the killer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.61,0:06:25.86,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We will also release a proclamation of cooperation in\norder to prevent bloodshed from misunderstandings.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.55,0:06:27.70,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Any objections?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.70,0:06:30.36,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Pointless. This is bullshit.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.36,0:06:31.69,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell did you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.69,0:06:38.19,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Refrain from foolish acts, Balalaika. I don't think\nit's your intent to blow this whole city apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.22,0:06:41.88,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Have you mistaken this for an\ninformal social gathering, Mr. Chang?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.26,0:06:45.01,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are we having a round of Gin Rummy next?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.72,0:06:52.05,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The reason I came here today was\nto clearly define our position.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.51,0:06:56.47,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hotel Moscow will show no mercy\nfor those who stand in its way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.86,0:07:03.86,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We will deny and then destroy them.\NFamily, friends, even the pet dog if necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.10,0:07:06.36,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Geez.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.83,0:07:12.61,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Look, everyone has a gun with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.13,0:07:16.50,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's like we wandered into the world of Clint Eastwood.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.12,0:07:22.17,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, there's some asshole out\nthere who thinks he's the Punisher.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.50,0:07:23.33,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Punisher...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.69,0:07:26.40,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...one who gives out punishment.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.17,0:07:29.06,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Punishment for what?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.47,0:07:33.76,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows. Right now, Roanapur is like popcorn.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.08,0:07:37.80,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's just waiting for enough heat to pop.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.50,0:07:46.84,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Did you hear Revy? There's a bounty.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.84,0:07:47.73,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How much?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.73,0:07:51.63,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,50,000, and not in our currency but in American dollars.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.63,0:07:55.65,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I guess they're getting serious now.\NShould we go after them?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.06,0:07:57.54,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know who it is yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.13,0:08:01.52,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Nope. But if it's an outsider, we'll know real quick.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.74,0:08:07.85,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, if it was an outsider we'd know\nright away. It's not that big of a city.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.38,0:08:10.45,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It was like that with Lovelace's maid.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.69,0:08:17.30,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And the fact that we haven't found out about\nit yet, means that someone's protecting them.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.30,0:08:19.16,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But we don't know who.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.46,0:08:21.39,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Now everyone's suspicious of each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.94,0:08:26.25,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well I really don't care, but I don't\nwant to get caught in the middle.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.93,0:08:28.67,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're worrying too much, Bao.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.00,0:08:32.99,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This place is a neutral zone. No\none's going to make a move.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.61,0:08:41.52,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yo, Two-Hands! You're drinking shitty booze again!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.00,0:08:43.25,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How's business?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.55,0:08:45.90,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Eda! Y-You bitch!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.90,0:08:46.55,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.11,0:08:50.13,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wait... y-you're the sister from the Church of Violence!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.59,0:08:53.67,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you have that cute guy with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.67,0:08:59.51,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hi, doing well? Want to play with me instead of\ndrinking with this wild boar of a woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.51,0:09:02.73,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't go fishing around for men\njust cause business dried up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.73,0:09:03.68,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.60,0:09:09.57,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Scarrry. Did you hear that, cute guy? She's been having irregular periods forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.36,0:09:13.32,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Eda, step outside. Just step outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.32,0:09:17.94,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be so tense, Two-Hands.\NI didn't come here to pick a fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.42,0:09:22.08,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I have a deal for you. A deal worth some money.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.08,0:09:24.06,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The manhunt, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.19,0:09:30.54,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Revy and I were just talking about that.\NThere's no one in this city that doesn't know already.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.74,0:09:34.93,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Shoot, really? How boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.93,0:09:39.43,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well then, let's get right down to it.\NThe anxious ones have already started.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.05,0:09:44.12,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The mafia is a given, but freelance\nassassins are also gathering here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.60,0:09:49.98,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,From what I hear, the Yun Brothers,\N"Big One" Emilio, and Ronny CK came into town.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.98,0:09:53.22,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Impressive. Those guys are at\nthe top of the killing business.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.22,0:10:01.23,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Others too. "Greentooth" Johnny was a joke though.\NHe came to us looking for an elephant gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.23,0:10:02.97,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What was he thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.29,0:10:06.10,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Does he think the target's a dinosaur?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.46,0:10:09.09,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If you shot a human with that, they'd just be dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.41,0:10:27.31,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well he's an exception. If we dick around, someone\nelse will get it. 50,000 is a lot to lose out on, Revy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.31,0:10:30.65,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No kidding. Got any more info, Eda?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.54,0:10:33.98,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I got one lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.70,0:10:39.81,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Early this morning, the Carribean\NBar on Bran Street got destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.49,0:10:42.66,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hotel Moscow is ready for war.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.30,0:10:47.67,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Fry Face is furious because of her dead subordinates.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.29,0:10:51.71,Style1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\frz5.5\bord0.1\shad.5\b1\c&H091313&\be1\fscx92\fnPad Thai\move(338,213,338,520,0,5450)\fs41}No Entry
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.50,0:11:32.33,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yo, thanks for the trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.59,0:11:35.49,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Do you have any information?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.49,0:11:39.28,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,One of the waiters survived, though he's nearly dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.83,0:11:45.07,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,To summarize, they came at four o'clock, near dawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.07,0:11:48.61,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Near-identical twins, dressed in\nwhat looked like mourning clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.61,0:11:52.39,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Creepy little brats, like in "The Shining".
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.49,0:11:57.32,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,When the bartender told them, "This is no place for kids.",
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.74,0:12:01.82,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,they took out your business card for the\NBougainvillaea Trade Company and said...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.55,0:12:06.40,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We meet guests for Miss Balalaika.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.40,0:12:10.45,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't she say that we would meet a guest here tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.24,0:12:13.69,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Go to the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.69,0:12:15.83,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, mister.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.21,0:12:21.26,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The guest will recognize us, when he sees us.\NWe're going to be in the corner here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.23,0:12:26.22,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If the bartender had called you then,\nhe wouldn't have died.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.07,0:12:30.85,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Unlucky for him, when he decided\nnot to bother you so late.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.78,0:12:38.36,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And then your collector arrived, right on time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.95,0:12:45.39,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He asked the bartender "How's business?"\NAnd the bartender replied, "Not that good."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.13,0:12:47.20,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,At that moment...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.23,0:12:50.37,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.00,0:12:53.00,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,will you play with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.26,0:12:58.24,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, mister. Let's play.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.28,0:13:08.93,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sahalov! It's them! They're the...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.44,0:13:23.38,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They figured out who we were.\NThey have good instincts, nee-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.38,0:13:23.94,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They certainly do.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.54,0:13:29.38,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We need to get better at this, nii-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.38,0:13:33.54,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be helped. What shall we do, nee-sama?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.84,0:13:36.50,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I guess it can't be helped...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.21,0:13:41.28,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Let's call down angels for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.63,0:13:46.77,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They say that Heaven is a good place. Right, nii-sama?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.23,0:14:03.73,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no! You're not allowed to run away.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.54,0:14:10.58,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Nee-sama! Let's take that guy home,\nso we can play with him until our next job!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.58,0:14:12.18,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Let's do that, nii-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.18,0:14:13.93,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, nee-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.40,0:14:16.67,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.13,0:14:23.32,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This guy is heavy, nee-sama. Help me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.32,0:14:27.43,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're a man, right nii-sama?\NLadies don't carry heavy things.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.43,0:14:34.35,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\frz5.5\bord0.1\shad.5\b1\c&H091313&\be1\fscx92\fnPad Thai\move(338,213,338,520,0,4100)\fs41}No Entry
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.63,0:14:37.26,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And once they moved the collector into their parked car,\nthey fired into the bar until there was no movement anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.92,0:14:41.81,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What sort of car was it? And the license plate number?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.32,0:14:48.28,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A black sedan. A Japanese car.\NWe're investigating its whereabouts.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.28,0:14:50.09,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, one more thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.59,0:14:53.54,Style1,,0000,0000,0000,,they were white, but don't have an English background.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.84,0:14:56.44,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They greeted everyone with weird phrases.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.82,0:14:59.42,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\fnEssai\fs25\fad(200,200)}Buna seara: "Good evening"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.82,0:14:59.42,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Like, "Buna seara".
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.78,0:15:07.04,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\fnEssai\fs25\fad(200,200)}Frate mai mic: "My little brother"\NSora mai mare: "My big sister"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.78,0:15:07.04,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And when they called each other they said,\N"Frate mai mic" and "Sora mai mare".
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.79,0:15:12.63,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Watsup, don't reveal this information to your superiors.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.01,0:15:15.47,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be a mess if the peacekeepers get involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.93,0:15:20.01,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I know. I like this city, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.69,0:15:28.15,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh yeah! Hey, Balalaika! We're going to join the\nhunt too! You'll pay the bounty to cops too, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.23,0:15:32.29,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What an unpleasant guy. He makes me sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.01,0:15:35.16,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But I've made a terrible mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.00,0:15:42.71,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I believed that if I made them act in two man cells,\nmy soldiers wouldn't get attacked.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.14,0:15:48.59,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I think Sahalov was taken by surprise, Kapitan.\NHe would've never dreamed that the assassins were children.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.41,0:15:53.42,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\fnEssai\fs25\fad(200,200)}Panjshir: A valley and battlefield in eastern Afghanistan
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.41,0:15:53.42,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This reminds me of Panjshir. Most of\nthe enemies there were children too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.55,0:15:59.45,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose souls can become thick. Ours are no exception.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.42,0:16:04.86,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed, Kapitan. We'll be more careful from now on.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.24,0:16:09.46,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Comrade, Sergeant. I do not wish for\nour forces to be weakened any further.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.46,0:16:14.84,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Use agents from outside our unit\nfor the search. Use them as pawns.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.84,0:16:15.28,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Ma'am
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.23,0:16:19.45,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's eight deaths for the cemetery so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.91,0:16:22.34,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how many get killed, I never get used to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.02,0:16:26.60,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,From the day of our oath, we were ready to die in battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.19,0:16:29.55,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I am certain Sahalov would feel the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.08,0:16:32.36,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I won't allow them to kill any more, Sergeant.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.36,0:16:36.46,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Those brats are going to pay for\NComrade Sahalov's life with their blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.09,0:16:39.43,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll kill them with the utmost of hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.29,0:16:44.44,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Geez.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.18,0:16:49.67,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How does it look? Have they been hung by anyone yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.67,0:16:52.27,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Not yet, but it doesn't look good.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.95,0:16:55.49,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,One mistake and they're screwed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.79,0:16:57.56,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A typhoon is nothing compared to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.53,0:17:01.45,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Balalaika's thinking of using the Visotoniki.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.96,0:17:03.02,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Visotoniki?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.02,0:17:06.29,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Stupid. Does she plan on turning this city upside down?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.16,0:17:15.09,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Their special troops, Visotoniki in Russian, were her\nsubordinates even before Hotel Moscow was around.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.39,0:17:20.72,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They function as a single killing machine,\nwith her as the brains.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.69,0:17:25.12,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They've had enough training to fight World War III.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.42,0:17:28.16,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Battle-hardened veterans from the Afghan war.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.16,0:17:30.94,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's why they're different from the other gangsters.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.94,0:17:33.61,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They're unified and have no mercy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.22,0:17:38.27,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to be anywhere\nnear them when they're serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.27,0:17:40.63,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,At least, not within 200 miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.00,0:17:48.75,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My mother has killed me. My father is eating me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.75,0:17:54.19,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My brothers and sisters sit under the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.19,0:17:59.12,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Picking up my bones, they will bury them.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.12,0:18:01.40,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Under the cold...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.93,0:18:03.89,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What in the hell are you guys doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.29,0:18:12.59,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We're changing clothes, of course. The blood's all dried up\nand sticks like glue, so we couldn't wear them anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.59,0:18:17.76,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's funny, you know. If you put nails\nin his head, it twitches like a fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.41,0:18:20.84,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It still moves even after he's stopped breathing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.37,0:18:23.20,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I think they call it "spinal reflex".
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.44,0:18:32.80,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The boss is so angry, he looks like a lobster!\NWe only told you to kill the Ivan bitch!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.80,0:18:35.80,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Who told you to kidnap her subordinate\nand turn him into a pin cushion?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.46,0:18:40.45,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's about time for you to finish up,\nand get the hell out of this city!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.45,0:18:42.59,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sick and tired of baby-sitting you two!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.71,0:18:49.28,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe those brats!\NIt's way beyond having a screw loose!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.28,0:18:51.79,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Maurry, they're really sick!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.79,0:18:57.73,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No kidding. We have to get rid of that mess too\nand can't even call the cleaners! Those idiots!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.53,0:19:03.08,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Could the killers realize who they're attacking?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.49,0:19:05.33,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They must be crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.65,0:19:08.75,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,These generations seldom appear. They're trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.22,0:19:15.34,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They're considered to be outsiders even\namong the garbage of the underground.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.93,0:19:20.36,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They usually do a lot of damage\nto everything and then disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.36,0:19:25.60,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But sometimes they survive,\nthanks to their bestial instincts or sharp wits.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.06,0:19:32.10,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They can't live without being over\nthe edge. And they spread disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.06,0:19:38.77,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If they're along those lines,\nit means they hate all sorts of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.77,0:19:46.00,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hating isn't the problem. They hate so many\nthings, they don't even know what they hate.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.62,0:19:50.71,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And in the end, they draw everything\naround them in and explode.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.03,0:19:58.65,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But only they really know for sure.\NThat's what I learned in the slammer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.24,0:20:05.85,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Rock! It's for you.\NFrom the person in the limelight, Miss Balalaika.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.10,0:20:10.17,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, nee-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.70,0:20:11.59,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.47,0:20:13.85,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What shall we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.25,0:20:19.00,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to try it. I've never put an Ivan in before.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.80,0:20:24.35,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Not that, nee-sama. About them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.33,0:20:29.67,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We can kill them eventually.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.58,0:20:33.33,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I don't like being yelled at or being struck.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.73,0:20:35.25,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It makes me want to cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.34,0:20:38.36,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Right, nii-sama?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.62,0:20:44.14,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"Buna seara." The nuance is like Italian, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.24,0:20:48.01,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you might know, because of your occupation.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.11,0:20:52.12,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My apologies, your previous occupation.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.42,0:20:55.01,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"Buna seara..."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.43,0:20:58.53,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How about the phrase, "Sora mai mare"?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.39,0:21:04.05,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me anything you can think of. Location? A name?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.05,0:21:07.78,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I remember someone from the European\nbranch telling me something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.40,0:21:10.88,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But I can't remember it clearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.47,0:21:18.69,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Vampire?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.00,0:21:21.01,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's that? What do you mean, Rock?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.45,0:21:24.83,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's it. It has to do with vampires.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.56,0:21:32.08,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It smell so strongly of blood, nii-sama. Let's take a bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.83,0:21:37.96,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But it smells so good. It's such a shame, nee-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.28,0:23:20.68,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The Chinese from the Lagoon Company.\NAnd the sister from the Church of Violence is with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.68,0:23:22.54,Style1,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If necessary, crush them underfoot.
